children.subject: If you’ve taken 134/135/153 then EECS 126 is a waste of time from what I’ve heard. You’re better off taking some more advanced stats course instead of 126

history.content: Stat 150 is more worth your time since the only thing you have not covered in EECS 126 is Random/Stochastic Processes. Also consider Stat210A/B if you want to delve deeper into theoretical statistics and learning theory.

children.subject: Posts @94 and @70 and @18 on the Stat001 Piazza (I think this link should work) would be useful for your consideration re: 126 vs 150 and some other possible interesting courses based on your background.
